\displaystyle\sum_{n=2}^\infty\frac {(-1)^n}{\sqrt{n}+(-1)^n} 
\sum_{n=2}^\infty \frac{(-1)^n}{\sqrt{n}+(-1)^n}=-\sum_{n=1}^\infty \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2n+1}-1}-\frac 1 {\sqrt{2n}+1}\right)
\rm HINT  \text{   }
\text{   } \displaystyle \sum_{n=2}^\infty \left(  \frac{(-1)^n   }{\sqrt{n}} -\frac{(-1)^n}{\sqrt{n}+(-1)^n} \right)= \sum_{n=2}^{\infty}  \frac{1}{n + (-1)^n \sqrt{n}} .
\left| \frac{(-1)^n}{\sqrt{n} + (-1)^n} \right| \ge \frac{1}{\sqrt{n}+1}
\sum_{n=2}^\infty \frac{1}{\sqrt{n}+1}
